 <div class="container">
  <h1>Contact and Bio</h1>
  <h2>Miguel Cardenas-Arroyo</h2>
<div class="body-text">
<img src="images/Miguel.jpg" alt="picture of an adult male dressed preppy in a brown sweater vest, white long sleeve button up shirt, and black pants">
<p> <strong>Miguel Cardenas-Arroyo</strong> <em>(he/him)</em> is a Latin-American writer, aspiring academic librarian and archivist from Los Angeles now living in New York City. They are a recent alum from NYU's XE: Experimental Humanities & Social Engagement program and are currently studying Library and Information Sciences with an advanced certificate in Archives at Pratt Institute. Their research interests are in queer and feminist practices, post-Marxist theory, and actively practices experimental writing. Their current work focuses on the interactions among Latine literature, queerness, memory, the body, and relations to home through experimental narratives. Cardenas-Arroyo views language as a catalyst for change and uncovers their truth through the act of writing. </p>
<p>Their favorite anime is <em>Frienren: Beyond Journey's End</em> because it is a look into the 'everyday' as a thousand year old elven mage realizes the beauty of connection. Their coffee order is four-shots of blonde espresso with coconut milk. Cardenas-Arroyo is a Sagittarius (to a fault) and is self-proclaimed French fry and ranch sommelier.</p> 
